ought. The sure-thing principle for decision under uncertainty and conjoint independence are identical in a mathematical sense. The mathematics underlying our three preference conditions has an older history. The independence condition for decision under risk can be recognized in the characterization of ?associative means,? and conjoint independence for multiattribute decisions in solutions to the ?generalized associativity functional equation.?
